    To verify that the edge states we have found [the non-degenerate unidirectional states in the rectangle of Fig.

     2b

    , two of which are shown in Fig.

     2c

    ] are indeed topological, we need to characterize our system through its Chern number. Since fractal lattices are nonperiodic, we calculate the real-space Chern number


      24

     ,

      25


    . Heuristically, the real-space Chern number “measures” the chirality of states at a specific quasi-energy, and in periodic systems, it yields the same integer number as the “standard” Chern number (defined on the momentum space)


      24

     ,

      25


    . The definition of the real-space Chern number is


